"18:42:8" : {s: 18, a: 42, w: 8, r: "نفق", t: "أَنفَقَ", l: "أَنفَقَ", lc: 68, tl: "anfaqa", lb: "খরচ করা ",e: "he (had) spent", b: "সে ব্যয় করেছে", f: 2, rm: "to be saleable, to come out of a hole, be exhausted (store), consumed, spent, expenditure. To enter into another hole where there is another outlet, so is a hypocrite who professes to believe first one thing and then another, thus entering faith through one door and leaving it through another."},
